@cjwizgeek Outside of Iris, the scene also gave us a really cool slow motion crash, showed us what Barry’s powers looked like to him while he was using them (with the assumption we haven’t seen the other film), and even pointed out why he needed a suit with his feet coming out of his shoes.

@cjwizgeek I think it will. When we see her again, we’ll know that they’ve crossed paths before and she knows he has powers. We won’t have to go through the typical meet/greet/reveal that other superhero love storylines (Superman/Lois) go through. We may get something different.
@cjwizgeek Remember she wasn’t a “random girl” to him. The whole scene was a take on the “time stands still when you meet the love of your life” thing.

@cjwizgeek The random person, particularly those who enjoy story beats versus action, *may* remember that Barry was smitten with a young woman and might wonder if he’ll ever see her again. They’ll recognize her again in a future film and may feel satisfied that they witnessed the prologue.

@cjwizgeek Eh. Iris’ scene established her as a character in the DCEU (the EU stands for *extended* universe), nodded to someone other than the JL knowing about Barry’s powers, made Barry more than just comic relief and secured a role for the only Black female DCEU principle actor so far.
